Colombia Stocks: Pacific Rubiales, Ecopetrol, Grupo Aval Rise

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-04-13T15:04:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/colombia-stocks-pacific-rubiales-ecopetrol-grupo-aval-rise.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 10:47 a.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index rose 0.5 percent to 14,268.96, while the
Colcap Index advanced 0.5 percent to 1,684.82.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp  (PREC CB) climbed 0.8 percent
to 53,800 pesos. The Toronto-based  oil company  with fields in
 Colombia  said it will reach daily production of 500,000 barrels
within five years, according to the daily La Republica.  Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores SA (AVAL CB), Colombia’s
biggest financial holding company, rose 0.8 percent to 1,345
pesos. The company will issue shares worth 2 trillion pesos
($1.1 billion) on April 25, according to an e-mailed statement
late yesterday. Demand for shares totaled about 3.1 trillion
pesos for the sale that began March 22, the statement said.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL CB), Colombia’s largest oil company,
rose 1.1 percent to 3,665 pesos, its largest increase since
March 28, as crude rose for the first time in three days.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
 Bschmidt16@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
